Comedian and campaigner Sarah Silverman was forced to apologize after she was caught exaggerating a story about being paid less than a man for a gig - to highlight the gender pay gap .
The comic and feminist campaigner recalled an incident at the New York Comedy Club when she claimed she was paid paid than her male counterpart , for a piece she recorded a wage-discrimination-activism video for Levo League .
But Silverman has apologize after New York owner Al Martin revealed the story was false , because she appeared as a guest on the show .